Senate President Ahmad Lawan yesterday got showers of encomiums as he celebrated his 63 birthday. The Yobe North senator became Senate President in June 2019 and has evinced great leadership traits as Chairman of the National Assembly. The Northern Governors’ Forum described him as a legislator per excellence and a patriotic Nigerian who has deployed his vast experience in politics for the good of the nation. Chairman of the forum and Plateau State Governor Simon Bako Lalong conveyed the North’s governors’ message to Lawan. He said Lawan has continued to provide purposeful leadership to the Ninth Senate by ensuring that the business of law-making is carried out with the overall interest of Nigerians.   2019 Report: Works Ministry to recover N1.174b from…     Court defers hearing in suit against Abba Kyari’s…     Fed Govt targets paperless govt system by 2030, says Pantami   - Advertisement - He hailed the Senate President for carrying along all his colleagues in the Red Chamber, irrespective of their party affiliations, and for ensuring that the Ninth National Assembly broke the jinx with the passage of landmark legislations, such as the Petroleum Industry Act (PIA) and the Electoral Act Amendment Bill, among others. Also, Kogi State Governor Yahaya Bello hailed Lawan for his selflessness, patriotism, commitment to duty and service to humanity. In a statement by his Chief Press Secretary, Onogwu Muhammed, the governor said Nigerians were proud of his patriotism of putting national interest above every other consideration. “On behalf of my family, the people and government of Kogi State, I wish to congratulate Your Excellency on the occasion of your 63rd birthday anniversary. “I must say that Nigerians are indeed proud of your rare display of patriotism and selflessness by ensuring that you always place national interest as uppermost in your leadership style as President of the Nigerian Senate.”